[goal]
Fix the auth redirect loop on full refresh.

[fold:context/summary]
JWT middleware races the cookie parser on refresh.

[fold:context/full]
Full repro + stack trace + 40 lines of investigation. requireAuth() reads state before
the cookie parser settles, which forces a redirect to /login even when the refresh token
is valid. Observed on main@da5e312.

[fold:constraints/summary]
Do not change login UI; preserve cookie names; regression test required.

[fold:constraints/full]
- Do not change the login UI (copy, layout, or redirects that aren't the bug).
- Preserve existing cookie names exactly — external integrations read them.
- Add a regression test that fails on main and passes on the fix.
- deny=filesystem.write(/etc/**)
END CRUMB
